		<h3>Daily Fiction</h3>
		<h1>The Beauty of the Days Gone By</h1>
		<h2>By Jason Stone</h2>
		<div class="img-excerpt-container">
			<div class="img-container"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/9780802167408.jpg" alt="The Beauty of the Days Gone By"></div>
			<div class="excerpt-container"><div class="excerpt"><em>The following is from Jason Stone's debut novel, </em>The Beauty of the Days Gone By<em>. Stone grew up in West Texas and graduated from the University of Texas at Austin. He lives in San Antonio. Inspired by real events, </em>The Beauty of the Days Gone By<em> is a vivid and sweeping Western in the grand tradition of </em>Lonesome Dove<em> and </em>Blood Meridian<em>: an unforgettable saga of fathers and sons, captivity and belonging, and the violent struggle among Texans, Comanche, and Kiowa in the years after the Civil War.</em></div></div>
		</div>
